1.  TYPE OF DATA

1.1  Parameter/Measurement.  Infrared and visible radiances measured in 20
spectral channels by the High Resolution Infrared Radiation Sounder
(HIRS/2).  HIRS/2 is one of the TIROS Operational Vertical Sounder (TOVS)
instruments on-board the NOAA TIROS-N series satellites.

1.2  Unit of Measurement.  Radiance in mW/(m**2)-steradian.

1.3  Data Source.  High Resolution Infrared Radiation Sounder (HIRS/2)
flown on-board the TIROS-N, NOAA-6, -7, -8, -9,-10, -11 and -12 spacecraft.

1.4  Data Set Identification.  TOVS HIRS/2 Level 1b Data Set.  Level 1b
data are raw data that have been quality controlled, assembled into
discrete data sets, and to which Earth location and calibration information
have been appended but not applied.

HIRS/2 Level 1b data are available in two data formats: full data set
format for all channels and an extract data set format for selective
channels.

2.  SPATIAL CHARACTERISTICS

2.1  Spatial Coverage.  The cross-track scan of HIRS/2 provides global
coverage of data for all 20 channels. The width of the cross-track scan is
99 degrees or 2240 km and consists of 56 steps.  Each scan takes 6.4
seconds, and there are 42 km between instantaneous field of views (IFOVs)
along the sub-orbital track.

2.2  Spatial Resolution.  The optical field of view (FOV) is 1.25 degrees
which gives a ground IFOV of 17.4 km diameter at the nadir. At the end of
the scan, the ground IFOV is 58.5 km cross-track by 29.9 km along-track.


