12.  RELATED DATA SETS

     1)  Information about two other TOVS instruments, the Microwave
         Sounding Unit (MSU) and the Stratospheric Sounding Unit (SSU), can
         be accessed through NCDS.  To access this information, specify the
         following data sets within the search criteria of the Data Access
         subsystem of the NCDS:

         TOVSMSU  (TOVS Microwave Sounding Unit)
         TOVSSSU  (TOVS Stratospheric Sounding Unit)

     2)  The Susskind TOVS data sets contain Level III geo-located
         geophysical data derived from the High Resolution Infrared
         Radiation (HIRS/2) and the Microwave Sounding Unit (MSU) sounding
         data.  These data sets exist online in Common Data Format (CDF).
         To access these CDFS, specify the following as input within the
         Data Applications subsystem of the NCDS:

                        NCDS$DATA:SUSSKND-TOVS_MONTH-FIELDS 
                        NCDS$DATA:SUSSKND-TOVS_MON-TEMP-PROF
                        NCDS$DATA:SUSSKND-TOVS_MON-H20-PROF
                     

